Slide 11 — Streamlit Apps Updating Data in Snowflake Tables
“Before this Streamlit application was developed, updates to the CFG_VW_CONTROL table were mainly handled manually through SQL updates.
This table is used as a control or gatekeeping table for reporting views. It controls when data should be exposed to end users by using MIN_DISPLAY_DATE and MAX_DISPLAY_DATE values.
Initially, the app was created as Version 1 with basic search and update functionality. Later, additional enhancements were added in Version 2 to improve audit handling and update efficiency.”
________________________________________
Slide 12 — CFG_VW_CONTROL App V1
“This was the initial version of the CFG_VW_CONTROL application.
The app was connected directly to the CFG_VW_CONTROL table in Snowflake.
The table stores configuration information such as:
•	PROGRAM_NAME 
•	VIEW_NAME 
•	MIN_DISPLAY_DATE 
•	MAX_DISPLAY_DATE 
•	USER_STORY 
•	COMMENTS 
•	Database and schema details. 
In Version 1, users could search records using either Program Name or View Name.
Once the record was identified, users were able to manually update the display date values directly through the Streamlit user interface.
However, audit columns such as UPDATE_DATE and UPDATE_USER still required improvement, which led to the Version 2 enhancements.”
________________________________________
Slide 13 — CFG_VW_CONTROL App V2 Enhancement
“After Version 1 was implemented, we did additional enhancements and created v2
One major enhancement was automated UPDATE_DATE handling. Instead of users manually updating timestamps, the application now automatically captures the current system timestamp during updates.
Another enhancement was automated UPDATE_USER handling. The application automatically captures the logged-in user information and populates the UPDATE_USER column.
To improve data integrity, editing of audit columns was restricted so users cannot manually modify those values.
Another important enhancement was updating only modified rows instead of updating the full dataset. The application now detects which rows were changed and updates only those specific records back into Snowflake.
These enhancements improved audit accuracy and reduced manual intervention
